Police operatives of TheFederal Capital Territory (FCT) Police Command on Friday arrested Abubakar Marshall, a lawyer to human rights activist, Omoyele Sowore, over failure to produce his client after bail. According to the FCT Police Public Relations Officer, DSP Josephine Adeh, was arrested on Friday and has been “charged to court following his failure to produce the suspect.” Recall that Sowore was on February 24, 2022 arrested by the police after a petition by the former House of Representatives member Prince Ned Nwoko over alleged publication of false news. Sowore To Make Presidential Declaration Next Week Sowore To Sue FG For Deactivating NIN He was granted an administrative bail through his lawyer Abubakar Marshall but failed to return to the police.